text: Naďa Mertová is an orienteering competitor who competed for Czechoslovakia. At the 1972 World Orienteering Championships in Jičín she placed 10th in the individual competition, and won a bronze medal in the relay with the Czechoslovak team together with Renata Vlachová and Anna Hanzlová. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:Czechoslovak orienteers Category:Female orienteers Category:Foot orienteers Category:World Orienteering Championships medalists
